ss\");\n            return Ok(None);\n        }\n\n        let body: IdentityResponse = resp.json().await?;\n\n        let signature: [u8; 64] = match BASE64_STANDARD.decode(&body.signature) {\n            Ok(bytes) => match bytes.try_into() {\n                Ok(arr) => arr,\n                Err(_) => return Ok(None),\n            },\n            Err(_) => return Ok(None),\n        };\n\n        for candidate in candidates {\n            let sign_data = build_identity_sign_data(&challenge, &candidate.to_bytes());\n            if candidate.verify_xeddsa(&sign_data, &signature) {\n                return Ok(Some(*candidate));\n            }\n        }\n\n        Ok(None)\n    }\n}\n\n/// Wrap IPv6 addresses in brackets for URL formatting.\nfn bracket_ipv6(addr: IpAddr) -> String {\n    match addr {\n        IpAddr::V4(v4) => v4.to_string(),\n        IpAddr::V6(v6) => format!(\"[{v6}]\"),\n    }\n}\n\n#[cfg(test)]\nmod tests {\n    use super::*;\n    use reme_discovery::RawDiscoveredPeer;\n    use reme_identity::Identity;\n    use std::collections::HashMap;\n    use std::time::Instant;\n\n    #[test]\n    fn bracket_ipv6_wraps_v6() {\n        let addr: IpAddr = \"::1\".parse().unwrap();\n        assert_eq!(bracket_ipv6(addr), \"[::1]\");\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn bracket_ipv6_leaves_v4() {\n        let addr: IpAddr = \"192.168.1.1\".parse().unwrap();\n        assert_eq!(bracket_ipv6(addr), \"192.168.1.1\");\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn controller_ignores_stranger_routing_key() {\n        let identity = Identity::generate();\n        let pubkey = *identity.public_id();\n        let rk = pubkey.routing_key();\n        let contacts = vec![(pubkey, *rk)];\n        let controller = DiscoveryController::new(contacts);\n\n        // A stranger's routing key shouldn't match\n        let stranger_rk = [0xFFu8; 16];\n        assert!(controller.contact_index.get(&stranger_rk).is_none());\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn controller_contact_index_groups_by_routing_key() {\n      